Budget Supermarket Warehouse Goods Registration Management System
1. System Overview

The Warehouse Goods Registration Management System (WGRMS) is an offline web-based application designed to help Budget Supermarket manage warehouse inventory efficiently. The system allows users to register goods, monitor stock levels, track stock history, and manage inventory activities through a structured interface.

The system improves inventory accuracy, reduces manual record errors, and provides quick access to warehouse information.

2. Key Features
User Authentication

User sign-up and login system.

Secure access to the system using registered accounts.

Logout functionality.

Dashboard (Home)

Overview of warehouse operations.

Displays:

Total goods in the system

Total stock value

Low stock alerts

Recent activities showing users who updated stock.

Goods List

Displays all registered goods.

Includes:

Product ID

Name

Description

Category

Quantity

Price

Search functionality to quickly find goods.

Add Goods

Users can add new goods to the warehouse inventory with the following fields:

Product Name

Category

Description

Quantity

Price

Stock History

Tracks all inventory changes including:

Product updates

Quantity changes

User who made the change

Date and time of activity

